efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(m) where m is the length of the word or prefix
space complexity: O(n) where n is the total number of characters in all inserted words
energy implications: LOW 
explanation: The Trie uses a dictionary to store characters and their corresponding child nodes.  Insertion, search, and prefix search all traverse the Trie in a linear fashion, resulting in O(m) time complexity. Space complexity is determined by the number of nodes in the Trie, which is proportional to the total number of characters in the inserted words.

